  "prompt": "What are some of the best YoPappuSoDumb memes?",
  "response": "YoPappuSoDumb is a meme format that originated from a Bollywood movie called *Badrinath Ki Dulhania*. The meme typically features the character Pappu, played by actor Varun Dhawan, in a scene where he looks particularly clueless or naive. The phrase \"Yo Pappu So Dumb\" is often used to caption the image, highlighting his apparent lack of awareness or intelligence.\n\nHere are some of the most popular and humorous **YoPappuSoDumb** meme variations:\n\n1. **Classic Relatable:**\n   - *Image*: Pappu with a confused expression.\n   - *Caption*: \"Yo Pappu so dumb, he thought WiFi was pronounced 'Wiffy.'\"\n\n2. **Tech Fails:**\n   - *Image*: Pappu staring blankly.\n   - *Caption*: \"Yo Pappu so dumb, he tried to screenshot his laptop screen with his phone.\"\n\n3. **Food Logic:**\n   - *Image*: Pappu looking puzzled.\n   - *Caption*: \"Yo Pappu so dumb, he thought Maggi was a vegetable.\"\n\n4. **School Humor:**\n   - *Image*: Pappu in the movie scene.\n   - *Caption*: \"Yo Pappu so dumb, he thought 'periods' were just punctuation marks.\"\n\n5. **Everyday Logic:**\n   - *Image*: Pappu with a blank stare.\n   - *Caption*: \"Yo Pappu so dumb, he tried to microwave a metal spoon to heat his tea.\"\n\n6. **Movie References:**\n   - *Image*: Pappu looking innocent.\n   - *Caption*: \"Yo Pappu so dumb, he thought *Kabir Singh* was a romantic comedy.\"\n\n7. **Social Media Fails:**\n   - *Image*: Pappu with a confused expression.\n   - *Caption*: \"Yo Pappu so dumb, he thought retweets meant he had to repost it manually.\"\n\nThese memes are lighthearted and often used to poke fun at everyday blunders or misunderstandings. The format works well because Pappu's expression perfectly captures the essence of someone being hilariously clueless. If you want to create your own, just pair his expression with a funny scenario!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
